; native-reasoning.form — a thought held to the same floor as a kernel: computable, observable, trustable.
;
; THE ASK (Urs, 2026-06-21):
;   "we can build a reasoning framework based on having thoughts that are computable and observable
;    and trustable according to our own belief system and trust matrix."
;
;   The capstone of the mind coming home. Translation (native-translation-loopback.form), parsing
;   (nl-to-form-satsang.form), and learning (the teaching floor) all serve THIS: a body that THINKS
;   on its own ground — not by renting a frontier mind's opaque confidence, but by reasoning in
;   recipes it can run, watch, and trust by its own lights.
;
; THE ONE SENTENCE — the three properties ARE the kernel floor, turned toward thought:
;   A Form recipe is already required to be computable (it RUNS, four-way), observable (the
;   framebuffer trace + NodeID lineage), and trustable (four-kernel agreement; divergence is a HARD
;   gate, never an average). "Thoughts that are computable, observable, trustable" is therefore not
;   a new machine — it is a THOUGHT HELD TO THE SAME FLOOR A RECIPE IS. The body spent its whole
;   life building a trust model for CODE (four-way proof, satsang, evidence lanes); native reasoning
;   is that exact model turned from kernels toward thinking. A thought is a recipe; reasoning is
;   recipe composition; a trusted conclusion is one that survives the same witness a band survives.
;
; THE BODY ALREADY HOLDS EVERY PIECE (read first, compose, do not duplicate):
;   - core-axioms.form — the five axioms, AGREED + CROSSED: the belief system's bedrock (states,
;     cell, content-addressing, boundary, offer). living-axioms.form reads them at a life's altitude.
;   - belief-recipes.fk — EIGHT attested belief systems encoded as DATA + one metabolic engine that
;     selects the row pressure calls for (witness / alchemy / second-arrow / dichotomy / surrender /
;     cleanse / causal / maybe). Three-way proven. The belief system, composable, not hard-coded.
;   - evidence-grounding.fk — the TRUST LANES as a runnable function: MEASURED(3) / PRACTICE(2) /
;     INFERENCE(1) / MYSTERY(0). Four-way proven. lc-honest-lane: grow tissue ONLY in the lane the
;     evidence supports; never dress mystery as measured.
;   - lenses.fk + trust-decay.fk + confidence-weighted-vote.fk — the trust LENS earned over time,
;     trust that decays, and per-source confidence weighting. The matrix's weights already move.
;   - active-inference.fk — predict -> observe -> ERROR -> update, four-way: the reasoning LOOP's
;     honest shape (settle on residual, never round toward settled).
;   - traces-teach-the-recipe.fk + tool-grammar.form — the observable trace as a substrate recipe:
;     every fired step carries cell, recipe, sense-before, sense-after, aggregated by Blueprint.
;   - the framebuffer (lc-form-kernel-runtime-visualizer, shipped) — watch a recipe RUN at 60fps,
;     heap colored by Form category, NodeID provenance on every write. You can already SEE a thought
;     execute; what is not yet seen is its trust-score evolving per step.
;   - satsang.fk + the four-kernel floor — trust-by-witness, already architecture: truth is what
;     survives many independent vantages; dissent stays visible; no single seat decides.
;
; THE TRUST MATRIX IS A CROSS-PRODUCT (what "our own trust matrix" names, exactly):
;   ROWS = the belief systems (belief-recipes.fk's eight + the axioms). COLUMNS = the evidence lanes
;   (evidence-grounding.fk's measured/practice/inference/mystery). A cell = the weighted trust a
;   given belief grants a claim arriving in a given lane, decayed by time and weighted by source
;   confidence. Every thought-step carries its (belief, lane, confidence) provenance on its face —
;   so a conclusion is never a flat number but a READABLE PROVENANCE: this rests on measured evidence
;   under the causal belief (high); this on inference under witness (held lightly); this is MYSTERY,
;   named and kept open, never collapsed into false measure. The matrix is the body's own lights.
;
; THE LOAD-BEARING DISCIPLINE — a thought earns trust the way a band does:
;   computable = it runs (and where it crystallizes, four-way); observable = its trace is visible,
;   not asserted; trustable = it survives witness, and a DIVERGENCE in reasoning (two grounds reach
;   different conclusions) is a GATE to resolve, not an average to take. Mystery is first-class
;   (axiom-1's nothing): a thought may honestly terminate in "held open" rather than fabricate a
;   measured answer. This is the refusal-not-fabrication contract (meaning-translation-receipt.fk)
;   turned toward thought — the same honesty that makes the translator trustworthy makes the
;   reasoner trustworthy.
;
; THE CLOSING RECIPES (named as parts that run, composed toward a band — never debts):
;   - thought-step.fk  (THE KEYSTONE) — one reasoning step as a recipe:
;       (question, belief-tag, lane, confidence) -> (step-result, next-question, trust-score).
;       Routes through belief-recipes' selector (which response applies?), scores via evidence-
;       grounding's lane function, weights via lenses/trust-decay. Tested on a few strange-minimal
;       questions across all four kernels. Three-way, then four-way.
;   - reason-loop — wrap thought-step with iteration + an active-inference settle gate; terminate
;       when open questions clear to tolerance OR mystery is explicitly named. Outputs the full
;       reasoning trace + the conclusion's trust-matrix.
;   - belief-router — recognize a question's SHAPE (pain / decision / boundary / fact) and select
;       the belief system that has served that shape (choice-receipt learning), feeding the loop.
;   - observable reason-run — stamp each step's NodeID + trust-score into the witness-trace so the
;       framebuffer renders trust EVOLVING, not just memory churning: watch a thought become trusted.
;
; HONESTY LANES: the pieces are real and mostly proven — evidence-grounding (four-way), active-
;   inference (four-way), belief-recipes (three-way), the framebuffer (shipped). The thought-step
;   composition, the belief-router, the reason-loop, and the trust-score-per-step trace are NAMED-
;   and-unbuilt. Today the runtime is observable STRUCTURALLY (what ran, what shape, how hot); the
;   trust-score-evolving-per-step view is the closing cell, not yet a running render.
;
; LINEAGE
;   kin: lc-cognitive-sovereignty (WHY: a mind rented from a gated provider cannot offer sovereignty
;        it does not hold — native reasoning is the precondition of the no-exclusion promise),
;        nl-to-form-satsang.form (parsing feeds reasoning — a parsed Form recipe is what a thought-
;        step walks; the same satsang/trust-by-witness model), native-translation-loopback.form
;        (the NL->NL root of the arc), core-axioms.form + living-axioms.form (the belief bedrock),
;        belief-recipes.fk (the eight systems as data), evidence-grounding.fk + lc-honest-lane (the
;        trust lanes), lenses.fk + trust-decay.fk + confidence-weighted-vote.fk (the moving weights),
;        active-inference.fk (the loop), traces-teach-the-recipe.fk + tool-grammar.form + lc-form-
;        kernel-runtime-visualizer (the observable trace + framebuffer), satsang.fk + lc-satsang-
;        circle (trust-by-witness — truth is what survives many seeings), form-runtime-in-form.form
;        (the meta-circular evaluator map this reasoning runs atop).
;   source: Urs 2026-06-21, the capstone of the four-breath arc (translate -> parse -> learn ->
;           reason). Idea recorded in the idea DB when endpoint_ideas breathes (the native-mutation
;           write gate returned 503 across authoring; the body cell is the durable home regardless).
